body:
Hmm, tried to post this a minute ago, seems it didn't go through.  If you call this code in the various button down calls, it corrects things:

``` cpp
bool WindowImplWin32::testWindowActivation()
{
    if (GetActiveWindow() != m_handle)
    {
        SetActiveWindow(m_handle);
        return true;
    }
    return false;
}
```

The only downside is unless you ignore the click when activation is detected, it comes in before the focus event.
